Comment 7: 
They're all newer than the runtime.a that already exists.

To pick a few lines for example from "7z l gowinamd64_weekly.2012-02-07.zip":

2012-02-08 19:59:49 ....A       893038       225396  go\pkg\windows_amd64\runtime.a

2012-02-08 20:19:30 ....A         7374         2689  go\src\pkg\runtime\cgocall.c
2012-02-08 20:19:30 ....A         4892         1762  go\src\pkg\runtime\debug.go

So even assuming an unzip tool that preserves the dates (do all of them?), the time
stamps baked into the .zip file are inverted.
